'''''Tournament Table''''' is a [[1978 in video gaming|1978]] [[arcade video game]] released by [[Atari, Inc.]] The [[Atari 2600|Atari VCS]] version is called ''[[Video Olympics]]''.

==Gameplay==
''Tournament Table'' is basically a multi-game arcade with several ''[[Pong]]'' variations. After inserting a coin, the player is prompted to choose one of the several games available.<ref>{{MobyGames|id=10177}}</ref> Those games are:
* ''[[Breakout (arcade game)|Breakout]]''
* ''[[Soccer]]'' (2 variations)
* ''Foozpong''
* ''[[Hockey]]'' (3 variations)
* ''Quadra Pong''
* ''[[American handball|Handball]]''
* ''[[Basketball]]'' (2 variations)

''Breakout'' is the only one-player game, the other being for two, three, or four players.

